</section>

<section class="experience">
    <div class="experience-media">
        <!-- Drop the experience image here: wwwroot/images/mineavrevr-experience.png -->
        <video autoplay loop muted playsinline>
            <source src="images/MineAwareGeneral2.webm" type="video/webm" />
        </video>
    </div>
    <div class="experience-text">
        <h2>The Experience?</h2>
        <p>The app features informational panels where you can read detailed descriptions and learn about various types of landmines and ERWs. These panels and their interactive objects provide essential knowledge to help you recognize and understand different threats.</p>
        <p>Additionally, there is an interactive practical area where you can apply what you've learned. In this section, you will explore simulated scenes, search for mines, and identify potential threats. This hands-on experience is designed to sharpen your detection skills and improve your ability to stay safe in real-world situations.</p>
    </div>
</section>

<section class="ukraine">
    <h2>MineAwareVR and Ukraine</h2>
    <p>The main inspiration for this project has been through the war in Ukraine. Our team of dedicated specialists working in and around the actual warzone have allowed us intimate knowledge of the situation and continues to inform us of how our app should function. It is our greatest wish that no one is harmed by landmines or Explosive Remnants of War. We will never provide virtual situations where the user can touch or play with any potentially dangerous object.</p>
    <p>Our hopes for MineAwareVR is that we can continue development to bring more functionality and more varied training scenarios to the application. With a portion of proceeds going to worthy Ukrainian causes, it's our genuine hope that we might also be able bring this training program to other platforms.</p>
</section>

<section class="developer">
    <h2>From the developer</h2>
    <p>It has been both rewarding and heartbreaking working on MineAwareVR, and my prayers and wishes go out to everyone who is currently suffering in this desperate and horrifying situation. I urge anyone who might be interested in garnering more knowledge about the conflict, or the current situation to check out these documentaries: "20 days in Mariupol" and to gain a deeper understanding of the history of what is going on, "Winter on Fire"</p>
